README for pulseaudio

NOTES

    0. ALSA configuration for PulseAudio

    install 'alsa-plugins' and add this to ~/.asoundrc:

    # Use PulseAudio by default
    pcm.!default {
        type pulse
        fallback "sysdefault"
        hint {
        show on
        description "Default ALSA Output (currently PulseAudio Sound Server)"
        }
    }

    ctl.!default {
        type pulse
        fallback "sysdefault"
    }

    1. Idle shutdown

    If you are not running a fully fledged DE you might have trouble
    with pulseaudio shutting down after being idle for a while.

    You can work around this by starting pulseaudio like this:

    pulseaudio --start --exit-idle-time=-1 --log-target=syslog &

    2. Bluetooth headsets

    For using bluetooth headsets, add the following command after
    starting the pulseaudio:

    pactl load-module module-bluetooth-discover &
